  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] Nuremberg was-- even though it was a city of almost 400,000, it was still a small town, and everybody knew everybody else, more or less.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And especially the Jews were known.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And the Germans knew exactly who was Jewish and who was not.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, nothing really before before Kristallnacht.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That's when things started to become physically dangerous.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "At that time, since the legal career was closed to me and singing also-- the singing career was also closed-- I joined my father's business and took care of the hops business and the brewery, to a far lesser extent.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That really was my father's department, but I was in the hops business, together with a cousin of mine whose father had been part owner.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And so we two were in the office together, and, together with my father, ran the business, which became more and more difficult because the Nazis made it almost impossible to conduct a business for Jews.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They, well, they came up in uniform, the SS, the SA, with all kinds of questions, and it just became extremely uncomfortable.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They would ask you about what you were doing, how you conducted your business.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They wanted to be sure that you didn't smuggle any money abroad, so they kept you under supervision.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it became almost impossible.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, it was a terrible situation, and in the end we realized that the only thing to do was to leave Germany.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But by that time, it was extremely difficult.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You need-- in order to get-- all the Jewish passports were taken away.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You could not have a passport unless you paid the so-called Reichsfluchtsteuer, literally Reich Flight Tax.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
